 ---
 
+## ML Algorithms — All Hand-Coded
+
+Every machine-learning algorithm in `backend/app/services/` is implemented from
+scratch with NumPy primitives only. **No `sklearn.linear_model.*`, `sklearn.tree.*`,
+or `sklearn.neighbors.*` is used.** scikit-learn appears in `requirements.txt`
+solely to load the bundled **Iris** and **Breast-Cancer** datasets (raw data,
+not algorithms).
+
+| Algorithm | Implementation |
+|---|---|
+| Linear Regression | Custom batch gradient descent with optional early stopping |
+| Polynomial Regression | Closed-form normal equation: θ = (XᵀX)⁻¹Xᵀy |
+| Ridge | Closed-form: (XᵀX + λI*)⁻¹Xᵀy (bias unpenalised) |
+| Lasso | Cyclic coordinate descent with soft-thresholding |
+| Elastic Net | Coordinate descent with mixed L1+L2 |
+| KNN | Pairwise distance + sorted-argpartition voting / weighted mean |
+| Decision Tree | Recursive CART: exhaustive split search on Gini/Entropy/MSE |
+| Genetic Algorithm | Real-coded GA with SBX crossover + polynomial mutation |
+| Datasets | Hand-coded `make_moons`, `make_circles`, `make_blobs`, `make_sine` |
+| Helpers | Custom `train_test_split`, accuracy and R² inline |
+
+`poly_degree` is honoured for **all five** regression algorithms — they share the
+same hand-built `polynomial_features([1, x, x², …])` design matrix.
+
+---
+
 ## Stack
 
 | Layer | Tech |
 |---|---|
-| Backend | Python 3.11+, FastAPI, Pydantic v2, scikit-learn, NumPy |
+| Backend | Python 3.11+, FastAPI, Pydantic v2, NumPy (algorithms hand-coded) |
 | Frontend | React 19, Tailwind CSS, Shadcn UI, Plotly.js, react-d3-tree, Zustand |
 | Math | KaTeX (react-katex) for theory drawer equations |
-| Tests | pytest (36 tests) |
+| Tests | pytest (40 tests, all passing) |
+
+---
+
+## Deployment
+
+### Backend → Render
+- New Web Service, connect this repo
+- Root Directory: `backend`
+- Build Command: `pip install -r requirements.txt`
+- Start Command: `uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT`
+- Add environment variable `CORS_ORIGINS` set to your Vercel URL, e.g. `https://your-app.vercel.app` (comma-separated for multiple)
+
+### Frontend → Vercel
+- Import this repo, Root Directory: `frontend`
+- Add environment variable `REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL` = your Render backend URL
+- Vercel auto-detects React and runs `yarn build`
+
+> **CORS:** the backend reads `CORS_ORIGINS` (comma-separated) from `.env`,
+> falling back to `http://localhost:3000` for dev. A regex via
+> `CORS_ORIGIN_REGEX` (default `https://.*\.vercel\.app`) is also applied so
+> Vercel preview deployments work out-of-the-box.
 
